            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-29T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-29T03:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW (Peace)/8–2947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-29T11:00:00+03:00">August 29, 1947—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2732. There follows Embassy translation Soviet note dated August 28, signed
                    Vyshinski received late last night: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In connection with your letter of August 18, 1947,<note n="1" xml:id="d353fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_561">p.
                                561</ref>.</note> I inform you that the government of the USSR has
                            presented to the Presidium of <pb facs="0583" n="565" xml:id="pg_565"/>
                            the Supreme Soviet of the USSR for ratification the peace treaties with
                            Italy, Rumania, Hungary and Bulgaria signed in Paris February 10,
                            1947.</p>
                        <p>The Soviet Government proceeding from the requirement for the deposit of
                            the instruments of ratification by the Soviet Union, USA and France in
                            Moscow and Paris, as provided for by the corresponding peace treaties,
                            on one and the same day, proposes to deposit the instruments of
                            ratification mentioned in the course of the next 10 to 15 days.</p>
                        <p>Concurrently with the present note similar notes are being sent to the
                            Embassies of Great Britain and France.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated London 314, Paris 315.</p>
                <p>Department pass Rome 76, Sofia 13, Bucharest 13, Budapest 18.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
